data.description:
Need a workshop ?!  We got it ! Super financing incentives on this home to make the payments better than rent! Lots  of storage in this charming affordable home nestled in a sought-after west Augusta location close to the Augusta National and the Augusta Canal nature trail.  adorable Home  , a fenced yard with shade and mature landscaping, beautiful sod , ***detached workshop/ garage,** and gorgeous original hardwood floors, this property offers the perfect blend of convenience and character. Great attic storage space  with walkup stairs.

Step inside to find a warm and inviting atmosphere, complemented by recent upgrades such as a new 30 year architectural roof and vinyl siding. The layout is designed to maximize both functionality and style, ensuring a seamless flow throughout the home.

Situated just moments away from the Augusta National, Lake Ulmstead, and Augusta Canal nature  Trail, this fantastic location provides endless opportunities for outdoor recreation and leisurely strolls. And with no HOA fees to worry about, you'll have the freedom to enjoy your property to the fullest.

Beyond its prime location, this home is an ideal investment opportunity, especially during the Masters tournament. Take advantage of its proximity to the Augusta National Golf Course and turn it into a lucrative rental property. Imagine the potential for substantial return on investment!

Inside, you'll find an array of desirable features, including refinished hardwood floors, living room with fireplace, eat in kitchen with pantry, a dining room, and a separate laundry room. Ceiling fans installed. Built in shelves, linen storage, and lots of attic storage. 

The kitchen boasts a pantry and all appliances, with a refrigerator,  washer and dryer also included for your convenience. Updated countertops in the kitchen. Updated bathroom shines with new lights, new fixtures,  new vanity, and updated shower with shelves and seat,

 updated vinyl siding, windows and a HUGE workshop with power, extra long parking pad .The front and back yards have been beautifully sodded, offering a lush and inviting outdoor space. Fenced yard with mature landscaping. Rocking chair front porch—perfect for relaxing after a long day or watching the rain. There is additional attic storage lots of floored storage space with a walkup stair case

To make this opportunity even more appealing, inquire about our incentive financing with a subsidized rate buy-down, and no PMI (qualifications  & income restrictions). We strive to provide you with the most favorable terms, ensuring a smooth and stress-free purchasing process.

Don't miss this fantastic investment opportunity that combines location, amenities, and affordability.  Embrace the charm and comfort of this home while reaping the benefits of its prime location and potential for a lucrative investment. 

**ask agent about great financing terms on this home with low money down!**
